'''Sadie Edon,''' sometimes credited as '''Sadie Eddon,''' or '''Sadie Eden''' was a regular stunt woman on the James Bond films before her role in [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope'']]. She played [[Garindan/Legends|Garindan]] and [[Reegesk/Legends|Reegesk]]. On the day of shooting, none of the regular background artists wanted to wear the [[Ranat]] suit, so Edon braved the extremely hot costume.

She is credited by [[John Mollo]] as portraying a "rodent" in [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope'']] as documented in the [[1979]] book [[The Art of Star Wars Episode IV: A New Hope|''The Art of Star Wars'']].<ref name="TAoSW">[[The Art of Star Wars Episode IV: A New Hope|''The Art of Star Wars'']]</ref>

